  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Aarti, I hope your day is going well. I wanted to check in and ask—did you try using your 'prop up your heart' trick while studying heart valves and music? How did it feel?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Yes, I tried it yesterday while I was studying. It helped me relax a bit, to be honest. I paired it with some classical music, like a Raga Yaman I was practicing. But I still feel a bit confused about the mitral valve. Maybe I need to prop up more? 😅"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "That sounds like a good try! You said it right, 'prop up your heart' — well done. Speaking of which, what part of the mitral valve is confusing? Maybe we can chat through it. Tell me more."
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "The structure, maybe? Like, how it opens and closes? I get confused between the mitral and tricuspid. Oh, and what exactly goes wrong in mitral valve prolapse? I've read it, but it doesn't stick. 😟"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You're doing great, just a tiny tweak — we say \"how it opens and closes.\" On that note, have you tried drawing the valves or using a simple word trick to remember the differences? What helps for you?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I tried drawing them once, but my diagrams are not so good. Maybe I need a better trick... like a funny sentence? Oh, and I like your idea of using words — can you help me with that? 😊"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Sure! Here's a quick trick: the mitral valve has two flaps (like a 'bi' — two), and the tricuspid has three (like 'tri' — three). Got it? What if we make a silly sentence for each? Want to try one together?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Yes, that makes sense! The \"bi\" and \"tri\" part, I can remember. Let's make a silly sentence — maybe something with \"bi\" like \"mitral is by the left\" or something? Hmm... not sure. You got a better idea? 😊"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You're doing great! Here's one: \"Mitral is by the left, just like my left hand is better at holding my chai.\" How does that feel? Want to make one for tricuspid next?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Lovely! The chai line is funny and makes sense. For tricuspid, maybe... \"Tricuspid has three flaps, like three spoons in my upma\"? Upma is a breakfast dish with lots of things in it — maybe too much? 😄"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Your sentence is creative and clear! We say \"like there are three spoons in my upma.\" Well done! Speaking of upma, what’s your favorite way to eat it? With sambar or something else?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I usually eat upma with sambar and coconut chutney — it’s my comfort breakfast. But sometimes I add some poha or broken wheat for extra protein. Helps me focus while studying! 😊"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "That sounds delicious and smart! You said \"helps me focus\" — perfect! On that note, does your study time always start with a good breakfast? Tell me more."
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Mostly, yes. I try to eat something before I start studying. It gives me energy, you know? But sometimes I get so stuck in a topic that I forget to eat. Then I have to prop up my heart all over again! 😅"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "I get that — study time can take over! You said \"prop up my heart\" perfectly. Speaking of which, what gives you the biggest energy lift during study breaks — music, snacks, or something else?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 9,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Music, definitely. Sometimes I just close my books, put on a little classical, and take a deep breath. It’s like my brain hits reset. But snacks are a close second — especially if it’s something sweet like jalebi! 😊"
    },
    {
      "turn": 9,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "That’s a nice balance — music and sweets! You said \"hits reset\" — very clear! Speaking of music, do you have a favorite raga to study with besides Yaman? Tell me more."
    },
    {
      "turn": 10,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I really like Bhairavi raga for studying — it feels very calming. But sometimes I mix it with Bhairav, especially in the morning. Oh, and sometimes I cook while listening to Kedar! It’s my marathi kitchen magic. 😄"
    },
    {
      "turn": 10,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Bhairavi and Bhairav are lovely choices! You said \"my Marathi kitchen magic\" — I love that phrase. On that note, do you cook for yourself every day, or only on special days? Tell me more."
    },
    {
      "turn": 11,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Most days, I cook for myself — it’s therapy, you know? But on busy study days, I just make something simple, like poha or misal. On Sundays, I make something special, like shengdana poha or a sweet like modak. It’s my way of treating myself! 🍲"
    },
    {
      "turn": 11,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "That sounds wonderful — cooking as therapy! You said \"it’s my way of treating myself\" — very natural! Speaking of Sundays, do you have any other special traditions for the weekend besides cooking? Tell me more."
    },
    {
      "turn": 12,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "On Sundays, I sometimes take a little walk or just sit with a book in my garden — if the weather is nice. It’s my way of switching off from all the books and diagrams. And yes, sometimes I just do nothing — which is probably the best tradition of all! 😊"
    },
    {
      "turn": 12,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "That sounds perfect — doing nothing is the best sometimes! You said \"switching off from all the books\" — very clear! Speaking of gardens, do you have any favorite plants or flowers there? Tell me more."
    }
  ],
